OL,3,CReport projects dramatic shortage in
OL,4,Chousing for registered workers
OL,6,FStatistics Jersey also projects a
OL,7,Fsevere deficit in two-bedroom homes
OL,8,Ffor buyers. In a baseline scenario,
OL,9,Fthere would be 640 too few "owner-
OL,10,Foccupied" houses of this type.
OL,12,FAcross all categories, the
OL,13,Forganisation forecasts that there will
OL,14,Fbe an anticipated shortfall of 1,510
OL,15,Fsmall sized dwelling units.
OL,17,FHowever, there is a large projected
OL,18,Fsurplus in owner-occupied, qualified,
OL,19,Fand non-qualified properties that have
OL,20,Ffour or more bedrooms.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/6
